<TITLE> CA becomes accessible by email </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 28 (bdnews24.com) Any citizen will now be able to establish contacts with chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed by using the CA's electronic mailing address, an official said Sunday. People should be able to lodge a complaint or give suggestions by emailing the CA, his press secretary Syed Fahim Munaim told bdnews24.com. The e-mail address is feedback@pmo.gov.bd and the website is www.cao.gov.bd/feedback/comments.php "One can express opinions about the caretaker government's activities and lodge any complaint about the state of affairs. Replies will be sent to the senders' addresses," Munaim said. If any person intends to advise the government on an issue in advance or one fears that certain governmental decisions might yield harmful results, the CA can be alerted as well, he said. bdnews24.com/
